Benue State Governor Samuel Ortom has scooped the Governor of the Year Award (Security) at the Independent Newspapers Award for his unrelenting efforts in the fight against insecurity in his state. Ortom, ably represented at the ceremony, received the award which held on Saturday evening at the Eko Hotel and Suites, Victoria Island, Lagos. Speaking after receiving the award, Ortom stated that the rest of the country had now seen what he had been alerting the nation about as insecurity had since spread across the country. #IndependentAwards: Middlechase Scoops Real Estate Company Ofâ€¦ BREAKING: Lagos Seals Event Centre Over Petrol Souvenir He called on the State and Federal Governments to do more to tackle insecurity across the country so that all Nigerians can live in peace.